AGGRESSIVE 2NL STRATEGY

Designed for maximum exploitation of loose-passive 2NL players.
Wide opens, aggressive 3-betting, big value bets.

OPEN RAISE (2.5bb)

UTG (16%):
77+, ATs+, KQs, AJo+

MP (22%):
66+, A9s+, A5s-A2s, KJs+, QJs, JTs, AJo+, KQo

CO (35%):
44+, A2s+, K9s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 76s, 65s, ATo+, KJo+, QJo

BTN (50%):
22+, A2s+, K5s+, Q7s+, J7s+, T7s+, 96s+, 85s+, 75s+, 64s+, 54s, A5o+, K9o+, QTo+, JTo, T9o

SB (28%):
55+, A2s+, K8s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 98s, 87s, A9o+, KTo+

VS SINGLE OPEN - 3-BET

3-bet value:
- vs UTG: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- vs MP: JJ+, AKs, AKo, AQs
- vs CO: TT+, AQs+, AKo, AJs
- vs BTN: 99+, AQs+, AKo, AJs, KQs

3-bet bluff:
- A5s-A2s, K9s

Call IP:
- 99-22, AJs-A9s, KQs-KTs, QJs-QTs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s, 76s

BB DEFENSE (wide)

vs BTN (defend 58%):
- 3-bet: TT+, AQs+, AKo, A5s-A4s
- Call: 99-22, A2s+, K8s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 76s, 65s, 54s, A8o+, KTo+, QTo+, JTo, T9o, 98o

vs CO (defend 50%):
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-44, AQs-A7s, KQs-KTs, QJs-QTs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s, AJo

vs UTG/MP (defend 42%):
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-66, AQs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs

VS 3-BET

4-bet/call: QQ+, AKs, AKo
Call IP: JJ, TT, 99, 88, AQs, AQo, AJs, KQs
Fold: rest

POSTFLOP (uses sonnet-style big bets)

Value hands - bet big, they call light:
- Nuts: 85-100% pot
- Sets/two pair: 75-85% pot
- TPTK: 75%/65%/55%
- Overpair: 70%/60%/50%

Draws:
- Combo draws: 70% pot semi-bluff
- Flush draw: check free, call 40% pot

Facing aggression:
- Flop raise: continue TPTK+
- Turn raise: continue two pair+
- River raise: fold one pair
